name: df-cncf
params: setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4, setvar s5, setvar s6
body: |- wceq(ccncf, cmpo(s0, s1, cpw(cc), cpw(cc), crab(s2, co(cv(s1), cmap, cv(s0)), wral(s3, cv(s0), wral(s4, crp, wrex(s5, crp, wral(s6, cv(s0), wi(wbr(cfv(cabs, co(cv(s3), cmin, cv(s6))), clt, cv(s5)), wbr(cfv(cabs, co(cfv(cv(s2), cv(s3)), cmin, cfv(cv(s2), cv(s6)))), clt, cv(s4))))))))))
comment: Define the operation whose value is a class of continuous complex functions. (Contributed by Paul Chapman, 11-Oct-2007.)
